{"parse":{"title":"Mel Thomson","pageid":58070568,"revid":860320216,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox biography vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\"><span class=\"fn\">Mel Thomson</span></th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alma&#160;mater</th><td>\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Melbourne\" title=\"University of Melbourne\">University of Melbourne</a> <br />\n</p>\n<a href=\"/wiki/University_of_York\" title=\"University of York\">University of York</a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<b>Scientific career</b></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Institutions</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Deakin_University\" title=\"Deakin University\">Deakin University</a> <br /></td></tr><tr style=\"display:none\"><td colspan=\"2\">\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Melanie (Mel) Thomson</b> is a microbiologist and science communicator based in <a href=\"/wiki/Victoria_(Australia)\" title=\"Victoria (Australia)\">Victoria (Australia)</a>. She is the General Manager of Education, Skills and Events at the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Medical_Technologies_and_Pharmaceuticals_Growth_Centre&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Medical Technologies and Pharmaceuticals Growth Centre (page does not exist)\">Medical Technologies and Pharmaceuticals Growth Centre</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Early_life_and_education\">Early life and education</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mel_Thomson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Early life and education\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Thomson went to Macclesfield Primary School and <a href=\"/wiki/Caulfield_Grammar_School\" title=\"Caulfield Grammar School\">Caulfield Grammar School</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:2_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:2-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> earned an Honours degree in <a href=\"/wiki/Microbiology\" title=\"Microbiology\">Microbiology</a> at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Melbourne\" title=\"University of Melbourne\">University of Melbourne</a> in 1998.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:0_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:0-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> She worked as a research assistant at <a href=\"/wiki/Great_Ormond_Street_Hospital\" title=\"Great Ormond Street Hospital\">Great Ormond Street Hospital</a>, developing treatments for life-threatening <a href=\"/wiki/Peanut_allergy\" title=\"Peanut allergy\">peanut allergies.</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-:1_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:1-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> She completed a <a href=\"/wiki/Biotechnology_and_Biological_Sciences_Research_Council\" title=\"Biotechnology and Biological Sciences Research Council\">Biotechnology and Biological Sciences Research Council</a> funded PhD at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_York\" title=\"University of York\">University of York</a> in 2009, working on the <a href=\"/wiki/Neisseria\" title=\"Neisseria\">neisseria</a> species.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:0_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:0-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Career\">Career</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mel_Thomson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Career\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>She worked at the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Leeds_Institute_of_Molecular_Medicine&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Leeds Institute of Molecular Medicine (page does not exist)\">Leeds Institute of Molecular Medicine</a> between 2009 and 2011, working with <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Jean_Crabtree&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Jean Crabtree (page does not exist)\">Jean Crabtree</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:1_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:1-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> She set up her own lab in the <a href=\"/wiki/Deakin_University\" title=\"Deakin University\">Deakin University</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Geelong\" title=\"Geelong\">Geelong</a> Centre for Emerging Infectious Diseases in 2011.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:0_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:0-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Thomson began to crowdfund for academic research, leading two successful campaigns <i>Mighty Maggots</i> and <i>Hips for Hipsters.</i><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> She took part in <i>\"I'm A Scientist, Get Me Out of Here!\"</i> in 2013.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:2_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:2-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> In 2014 she was diagnosed with <a href=\"/wiki/Multiple_sclerosis\" title=\"Multiple sclerosis\">multiple sclerosis</a> and has since become an advocate for patients.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> She joined the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Medical_Technologies_and_Pharmaceuticals_Growth_Centre&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Medical Technologies and Pharmaceuticals Growth Centre (page does not exist)\">Medical Technologies and Pharmaceuticals Growth Centre</a> (MTPConnect) in 2016 as General Manager for education.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:0_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:0-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> MTPConnect is a med-tech and pharma growth centre.<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>She is a foundering steering member of Women in Science Australia.<sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>She won the Telstra Victorian Public Sector and Academia Award in 2017.<sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> She won the Leadership Award at the 2017 Geelong Awards for People with a Disability.<sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In September 2018 she sparked controversy by referring to Qantas staff as \"trolly dollys\" in a tweet.<sup id=\"cite_ref-14\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mel_Thomson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-:2-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-:2_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-:2_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://microa13.imascientist.org.au/profile/melaniethomson/\">\"Profile \u2013 Micro Life Zone\"</a>. <i>microa13.imascientist.org.au</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2018-08-04</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=microa13.imascientist.org.au&amp;rft.atitle=Profile+%E2%80%93+Micro+Life+Zone&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fmicroa13.imascientist.org.a